lead_paragraph: Lara Gut made her World Cup overall title official despite finishing 13th in the final downhill of the season on Wednesday, and Peter Fill became the first Italian to win the men’s downhill title.
snippet: Lara Gut made her World Cup overall title official despite finishing 13th in the final downhill of the season on Wednesday, and Peter Fill became the first Italian to win the men’s downhill title.
abstract: Swiss skiier Lara Gut wins overall World Cup title, despite 13th-place finish in season's final downhill in St Moritz, Switzerland.
